        "## Toyota car price prediction"
      ]
    },
    {

      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "kqofsuj-FdQz"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Introduction:\n",
        "The dataset provided here consist of Toyota UK Car- related attributes, which is collected from Kaggle (https://rb.gy/owtkqf).\n",
        "The 'toyota.csv' dataset contains various features of Toyota cars, likely including attributes such as model, year, mileage, engine size, fuel type, and other specifications. This information can be used to analyze and predict the price(£) of Toyota cars based on these features.\n",
        "In this analysis, We have done a basic EDA of car features and we have selected best features for predicting the price(£) of the car."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "-FA3Fvnddzl3"
      },
      "source": [
        "- Explanation of each attribute in the dataset:\n",
        "\n",
        "1) model: The specific model of the car (e.g., GT86).\n",
        "2) year: The year the car was manufactured.\n",
        "3) price: The price of the car (pounds).\n",
        "4) transmission: The type of transmission in the car (e.g., Manual, Automatic, Semi-Auto, Other).\n",
        "5) mileage: The total distance the car has traveled (usually in miles or kilometers).\n",
        "6) fuelType: The type of fuel the car uses (e.g., Petrol, Diesel, Hybrid).\n",
        "7) tax: The amount of tax paid for the car (likely an annual value).\n",
        "8) mpg: The car's fuel efficiency measured in miles per gallon.\n",
        "9) engineSize: The size of the engine, usually measured in liters."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "csGZHt5aFdQ0"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Problem statement:\n",
        "\n",
        "The primary purpose of using this dataset is to predict used car price based on features provided by user. By leveraging the attributes provided in the dataset, we aim to build a predictive model that can estimate the price(£) of Toyota cars.\n",
        "- We will use different Regression models like (Linear regression model, Multiple Linear Regression model, Decision Tree, Random forest resression) for the price prediction."
      ]
    },

              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-6caa9001-337c-439a-a1c2-7a4d447b439f');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "    </script>\n",

              "      const quickchartButtonEl =\n",
              "        document.querySelector('#' + key + ' button');\n",
              "      quickchartButtonEl.disabled = true;  // To prevent multiple clicks.\n",

              "      try {\n",
              "        const charts = await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction(\n",
              "            'suggestCharts', [key], {});\n",
              "      } catch (error) {\n",
              "        console.error('Error during call to suggestCharts:', error);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "      quickchartButtonEl.classList.remove('colab-df-spinner');\n",
              "      quickchartButtonEl.classList.add('colab-df-quickchart-complete');\n",

              "\n",
              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-a588fd37-e3b3-4ece-8ddd-dbba504c6eb5');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "    </script>\n",
              "  </div>\n",

              "</style>\n",
              "\n",
              "  <script>\n",
              "    async function quickchart(key) {\n",
              "      const quickchartButtonEl =\n",
              "        document.querySelector('#' + key + ' button');\n",
              "      quickchartButtonEl.disabled = true;  // To prevent multiple clicks.\n",
              "      quickchartButtonEl.classList.add('colab-df-spinner');\n",
              "      try {\n",
              "        const charts = await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction(\n",
              "            'suggestCharts', [key], {});\n",
              "      } catch (error) {\n",
              "        console.error('Error during call to suggestCharts:', error);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "      quickchartButtonEl.classList.remove('colab-df-spinner');\n",
              "      quickchartButtonEl.classList.add('colab-df-quickchart-complete');\n",
              "    }\n",
              "    (() => {\n",
              "      let quickchartButtonEl =\n",
              "        document.querySelector('#df-c9064aa9-4d91-4927-abbd-9d4554fc1a97 button');\n",
              "      quickchartButtonEl.style.display =\n",
              "        google.colab.kernel.accessAllowed ? 'block' : 'none';\n",
              "    })();\n",
              "  </script>\n",
              "</div>\n",
              "\n",
              "    </div>\n",
              "  </div>\n"
            ],
            "application/vnd.google.colaboratory.intrinsic+json": {

              "      buttonEl.style.display =\n",
              "        google.colab.kernel.accessAllowed ? 'block' : 'none';\n",
              "\n",
              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-b4b19fcf-b9d7-44f9-a889-8f3923e8ad2c');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "    </script>\n",
              "  </div>\n",
              "\n",
              "\n",

        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 1000x300 with 1 Axes>"
            ],
            "image/png": "\n"
          },
          "metadata": {}
        },
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Polynomial Degree 4\n",
            "Mean Squared Error of Validation Set: 22243279.027454164\n",
            "Mean Absolute Error of Validation Set: 1205.4734919978098\n",
            "R2 Score of Validation Set: 0.39564263455121185\n",
            "\n",
            "Mean Squared Error of Test Set: 34294610.41361025\n",
            "Mean Absolute Error of Test Set: 1142.3321095317046\n",
            "R2 Score of Test Set: 0.08306769960726168\n",
            "\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import PolynomialFeatures\n",
        "max_degree = 5\n",
        "for degree in range(1, max_degree):\n",
        "    poly_features = PolynomialFeatures(degree=degree)\n",
        "    x_train_poly = poly_features.fit_transform(x_train)\n",
        "    x_val_poly = poly_features.transform(x_val)\n",
        "    x_test_poly = poly_features.transform(x_test)\n",
        "\n",
        "    model0 = LinearRegression()\n",
        "    model0.fit(x_train_poly, y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # prediction\n",
        "    y_val_predict = model0.predict(x_val_poly)\n",
        "    y_test_predict = model0.predict(x_test_poly)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # plot\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 3))\n",
        "    plt.scatter(y_val, y_val_predict, marker='+', label='y_val_predict', color='r')\n",
        "    plt.scatter(y_test, y_test_predict, marker='+', label='y_test_predict', color='black')\n",
        "    plt.xlabel('Actual Target Variable')\n",
        "    plt.ylabel('Predicted Target Variable')\n",
        "    plt.title(f'Actual(y) vs Predicted(y) for Polynomial Degree {degree}')\n",
        "    plt.legend()\n",
        "    plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Evaluation on the validation set\n",
        "    p_mse_val = mean_squared_error(y_val, y_val_predict)\n",
        "    p_mae_val = mean_absolute_error(y_val, y_val_predict)\n",
        "    p_R2_val = r2_score(y_val, y_val_predict)\n",
        "    print(f\"Polynomial Degree {degree}\")\n",
        "    print(f\"Mean Squared Error of Validation Set: {p_mse_val}\")\n",
        "    print(f\"Mean Absolute Error of Validation Set: {p_mae_val}\")\n",
        "    print(f\"R2 Score of Validation Set: {p_R2_val}\")\n",
        "    print()\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Evaluation on the test set\n",
        "    p_mse_test = mean_squared_error(y_test, y_test_predict)\n",
        "    p_mae_test = mean_absolute_error(y_test, y_test_predict)\n",
        "    p_R2_test = r2_score(y_test, y_test_predict)\n",
        "    print(f\"Mean Squared Error of Test Set: {p_mse_test}\")\n",
        "    print(f\"Mean Absolute Error of Test Set: {p_mae_test}\")\n",
        "    print(f\"R2 Score of Test Set: {p_R2_test}\")\n",
        "    print()\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ElyNIR2NdzmE"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Conclusion:**\n",
        "- For degree=2, r2_score is maximum which is 0.95, implies that 95% of variance in the car price data is explained by the model.\n",
        "  And as we increase the degree the model accuray decreases because of overfitting of the data."
      ]
    },

        "x = df_encoded.drop('price', axis=1)\n",
        "y = df_encoded['price']"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 34,

        "id": "fiwVd7IEFdRL"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Split the data into 80% training, 10% validation, and 10% test sets\n",
        "x_train, x_temp, y_train, y_temp = train_test_split(x, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=45)\n",
        "x_val, x_test, y_val, y_test = train_test_split(x_temp, y_temp, test_size=0.5, random_state=45)"
      ]
    },
    {

        "###     Multiple Linear Regression"

    {

      "execution_count": 36,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Uh4Wgd2RFdRM",
        "outputId": "319d5a22-21f1-48aa-feca-dffc90c247c9",

        "# Train a linear regression model\n",
        "model1 = LinearRegression()\n",
        "model1.fit(x_train, y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Predict on validation and test sets\n",
        "y_val_pred_mlr = model1.predict(x_val)\n",
        "y_test_pred_mlr = model1.predict(x_test)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Scatter Plot\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(10,3))\n",
        "plt.scatter(y_val,y_val_pred_mlr,marker='+',color='red',alpha=0.5,label='y1_val_pred_mlr')\n",
        "plt.scatter(y_test,y_test_pred_mlr,marker='+',color='g',alpha=0.7,label='y1_test_pred_mlr')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('actual target variable')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('predicted target variable')\n",
        "plt.title('Actual(y) vs Predicted(y)')\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 37,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "noV7kjQNFdRN",

            ]
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 37
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Evaluate the model on the validation set\n",
        "mlr_mse_val = mean_squared_error(y_val, y_val_pred_mlr)\n",
        "mlr_mae_val = mean_absolute_error(y_val, y_val_pred_mlr)\n",
        "mlr_r2_val = r2_score(y_val, y_val_pred_mlr)\n",
        "mlr_mse_val, mlr_mae_val, mlr_r2_val"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 38,

        "plt.xlabel('actual target variable')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('predicted target variable')\n",
        "plt.title('Actual(y) vs Predicted(y)')\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.show()"

      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "QDg5cPH7LTVs"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Final Summary:"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "MXHdvVikLYWw"
      },
      "source": [
        "- **Polynomial Regression**:\n",
        "  - **R² Score**: 0.95\n",
        "  - **Interpretation**: Approximately 95% of the variance in car prices is explained by the predictors, indicating a strong relationship between the features and car prices.\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Multiple Linear Regression**:\n",
        "  - **R² Score**: 0.93\n",
        "  - **Interpretation**: Approximately 93% of the variance in car prices is explained by the predictors, indicating a strong relationship between the features and car prices.\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Decision Tree Regression**:\n",
        "  - **R² Score**: 0.94\n",
        "  - **Interpretation**: Around 94% of the variance in car prices is explained by the predictors, suggesting a strong relationship, slightly better than multiple linear regression.\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Random Forest Regression**:\n",
        "  - **R² Score**: 0.96\n",
        "  - **Interpretation**: 96% of the variance in car prices is explained by the predictors, showing the strongest relationship among all the models tested.\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Overall Conclusion**:\n",
        "  - **Best Model**: Random Forest, as it achieved the highest R² score (0.96), indicating that it best captures the variance in car prices among the three models applied."
      ]
